Recent work has demonstrated that GPT-3 is a strong few-shot learner [NEURIPS2020_1457c0d6]. Herein, we are interested in how well our classifier-constrained methods compare to the GPT-3 with prompted examples. 
We prompt GPT-3 with four examples for each (positive, negative) class from one dataset (e.g., TRT) and evaluate on other datasets (e.g., RSDD, eRisk). Due to the high computational cost of GPT-3, we only evaluate on {{arxiv_2204_10432_FO0023||FO}} positive samples and {{arxiv_2204_10432_FO0024||FO}} negative samples from each dataset.